🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we invited @noznozawa, founder of San Francisco’s Noz Design. Tune in for Noz’s take on how to create a home you love (while putting to the side, at least for the moment, the resale value) — plus her favorite color combinations, post-pandemic home design, and the difference between “Asian Art” and “Modern Architecture from 1940 to 1945”. Featuring a vessel from @angusandceleste! \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.text: Venezuela-born artist @r.sanguino, who works chiefly in ceramics, makes gorgeous, expressive objects. He joins us for this week’s Milkshake from his studio in New York City — and talks to us about coming to the US right after art school in Caracas, how his practice has changed over the past year, and how #crossfit has (literally) shaped his work. \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.title: DMTV Milkshake: Channeling the Energy of New York

node.text: Max Lamb is known for his direct yet playful approach to working with materials, as shown in his third solo show at Salon 94 Design that’s on exhibit through September 11th. Its title – Wood, Stone – represents the two bodies of work it includes, one using western red cedar and the other stone, both crafted using ancient and modern techniques to reach their finished state. \\\ Read more about Max Lamb's latest creations and schedule an appointment to visit the exhibition at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: @lyledc is a minimalist hotel located in Washington, D.C., designed by @loregrouplondon. Creative director Jacu Strauss found luxury within the details of this building’s original Art Deco features. By embracing these elements, he wanted to create a place of calm and comfort, mixed with understated style. Strauss created spaces that are comfortable and calming in neutral tones for the rooms and penthouse suite, featuring natural materials including burl wood Art Deco headboards, rattan seating and berber carpets. \\\ Read more about the Lyle in this week's Skim Milk at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: South London-based furniture brand @janhendzelstudio recently released its first-ever full collection, Bowater. Comprising nine pieces, the collection highlights the beauty of homegrown British timber, celebrates British craftsmanship and champions ideals about sustainability in design work. Bowater consists of a chest of drawers, stools, side tables, shelving, a work desk, a media unit, desk tidies/trays and a few other decorative objects. Only British woods were used in this collection, including olive ash, Sycamore and two other new materials called ‘Baked’ Ash and ‘Baked’ Sycamore that have undergone a Thermo modification process that makes the wood more durable. \\\ Read more about the playful and impressive Bowater collection at the link in bio. 🔗
